WEBVTT

00:01.602 --> 00:04.202
I lost the caterer,
all my deposits.

00:04.204 --> 00:06.138
Why did I have to give
my stupid student teacher

00:06.140 --> 00:07.672
so many
wedding responsibilities?

00:07.674 --> 00:09.808
It's not your fault.
You can't blame yourself.

00:09.810 --> 00:11.676
You see the best in people.

00:11.678 --> 00:14.146
No, it is my fault!
It is!
Ow!

00:14.148 --> 00:17.149
Loren: I always see
the best in people.
Hey, Quinn,
what are you doing?

00:17.151 --> 00:20.285
It's goddamn...
Great news!
Your friends are here!

00:20.287 --> 00:22.887
And they just said they're
willing to do whatever it takes

00:22.889 --> 00:25.290
to throw you a wedding
right here at Smoot.

00:25.292 --> 00:26.024
Isn't that right, guys?

00:26.026 --> 00:27.292
No.         No.

00:27.294 --> 00:28.761
Please.
I will do anything.

00:28.763 --> 00:30.895
All right, fine, I want
retroactive paternity leave --

00:30.897 --> 00:32.497
whatever they get
in Scandinavia.

00:32.499 --> 00:33.565
Paternity.
10 days paid vacation

00:33.567 --> 00:35.700
and I get to plan
the wedding -- like J.Lo!

00:35.702 --> 00:36.568
Who is that?

00:36.570 --> 00:38.036
I want to work
through the summer,

00:38.038 --> 00:40.505
and I want to be one of the guys
in the suits carrying the box.

00:40.507 --> 00:41.774
Are you talking
about a funeral?

00:41.776 --> 00:43.575
I'm afraid
this is non-negotiable.

00:43.577 --> 00:44.909
Fine.

00:44.911 --> 00:46.511
All right!
Everyone's in!

00:46.513 --> 00:48.713
And they're doing it
genuinely?

00:48.715 --> 00:50.382
They didn't need
any bribing or anything?

00:50.384 --> 00:51.784
Nope, not at all.

00:51.786 --> 00:53.986
I know if
the situation was reversed,

00:53.988 --> 00:56.188
I'd probably need, like,
a bunch of days off.

00:56.190 --> 00:57.790
You know, whatever
they get in Scandinavia.

00:57.792 --> 01:00.725
Loren, just come out.

01:00.727 --> 01:02.927
[ Sniffles ]
Okay, I'll do it

01:02.929 --> 01:04.463
with the help of
my good friends.

01:04.465 --> 01:06.799
And I want you to know,
I'd do the same for you.

01:06.801 --> 01:09.802
Well, you guys heard it from
the handsome groom himself.

01:09.804 --> 01:11.936
It's going to be
a Smoot wedding!

01:11.938 --> 01:13.472
Good news.
I get to carry your body.

01:13.474 --> 01:16.008
I don't want him
carrying my body.

01:16.010 --> 01:18.076
Well, it's non-negotiable,
Loren.

01:18.078 --> 01:19.344
♪♪

01:19.346 --> 01:21.613
♪ Quit wasting my time ♪

01:21.615 --> 01:24.216
♪ I ain't here for you ♪

01:24.218 --> 01:26.418
♪ I'm just putting in work ♪

01:26.420 --> 01:32.157
♪ Till my day is through ♪

01:32.159 --> 01:33.692
Now I know the fact
that I'm engaged

01:33.694 --> 01:36.361
to a high-end escort
might ruffle the feathers

01:36.363 --> 01:38.163
of certain staid town elders,

01:38.165 --> 01:41.433
but I like to think of myself as
a modern-day Toulouse Lautrec.

01:41.435 --> 01:42.634
Abbey: Yep.

01:42.636 --> 01:45.770
Except, not a dwarf,
but still very talented.

01:45.772 --> 01:48.240
Anyway, it's all very woke,

01:48.242 --> 01:49.708
which is why I was
trying to give Jade

01:49.710 --> 01:51.776
the fairytale wedding
she's always dreamed of,

01:51.778 --> 01:54.847
but now I'm stuck here
with you assholes.

01:54.849 --> 01:55.848
So this is a pivot --

01:55.850 --> 01:58.583
Okay, what my client
is trying to say

01:58.585 --> 02:00.785
is that your wedding day

02:00.787 --> 02:03.055
is the single most-important
day of your life.

02:03.057 --> 02:04.322
Exactly, that's it.
That's all I'm trying to say.

02:04.324 --> 02:06.725
I mean, I remember
on my wedding day thinking,

02:06.727 --> 02:10.128
[ Chuckles ] "You know,
about time Abbey Rabinowitz

02:10.130 --> 02:12.397
gets a little piece
of this so-called 'happiness.'"

02:12.399 --> 02:13.598
[ Laughs ]

02:13.600 --> 02:15.067
You know, of course,
14 months in,

02:15.069 --> 02:18.937
one Big Ol' Yam's
waitress later, it's poof!

02:18.939 --> 02:21.940
But that's why we need
all hands on deck.

02:21.942 --> 02:23.608
-Yep.
-Rod?

02:23.610 --> 02:26.945
Apps and mains for,
like, 80 to 100 people.

02:26.947 --> 02:30.148
Rod, not "apps and mains."
Elevated farm-to-table cuisine.

02:30.150 --> 02:32.284
I don't know what that means.
And rubber gloves, dude.

02:32.286 --> 02:33.485
I'm serious.

02:33.487 --> 02:35.019
Leslie, how's
the wedding attire going?

02:35.021 --> 02:38.290
I got some of my students on it
right now for extra credit.

02:38.292 --> 02:41.025
Why am I doing the flowers?
I don't even like Loren.

02:41.027 --> 02:43.628
And you've got me buying
his prostitute a bouquet.

02:43.630 --> 02:48.032
Jade is not Loren's sex worker,
she is Loren's fiancée.

02:48.034 --> 02:50.903
She is everyone else's
sex worker.
Thank you.

02:50.905 --> 02:53.505
And you're talking
to Shoemaker about the music.
Totally. Yep.

02:53.507 --> 02:54.973
So I think we're all set!
I think we're good.

02:54.975 --> 02:58.243
Oh, I need a job because
there's no coffin to carry.

02:58.245 --> 03:02.915
You know, you have, uh,
the most important job of all.

03:02.917 --> 03:04.116
Best man?
No.

03:04.118 --> 03:05.517
Groom?
No.

03:05.519 --> 03:08.853
Finding cans to tie on the back
of the bride and groom's car!

03:08.855 --> 03:09.854
-Hey!
-Yes!

03:09.856 --> 03:10.923
Yeah.

03:10.925 --> 03:12.457
Sounds like a real mission.

03:12.459 --> 03:14.927
All right? Go out there,
and knock it out of the park.

03:14.929 --> 03:16.060
Yes!
Okay?

03:16.062 --> 03:16.929
Let's do it!

03:16.931 --> 03:19.063
Yeah.
Everybody go.

03:19.065 --> 03:21.466
Yeah.
That went great.

03:21.468 --> 03:22.935
I think
we're on board here.

03:22.937 --> 03:26.805
Looks like it's all
really coming together.

03:26.807 --> 03:28.741
Quinn,
you don't think I'd forget

03:28.743 --> 03:31.743
about my best work friend,
do you?

03:31.745 --> 03:33.545
If it wasn't for you,

03:33.547 --> 03:35.280
I would have
never even met Jade,

03:35.282 --> 03:38.817
which is why I would be honored
if you would marry us.

03:38.819 --> 03:42.220
You...want me...

03:42.222 --> 03:43.888
to officiate your wedding?

03:43.890 --> 03:46.424
<i> We</i> want you
to officiate our wedding.

03:46.426 --> 03:48.493
Loren, it would be
such an honor.

03:48.495 --> 03:50.295
Okay.
I do!

03:50.297 --> 03:51.896
All right.
I do!

03:51.898 --> 03:53.966
♪♪

03:53.968 --> 03:55.634
No, I'm not going to book
your band

03:55.636 --> 03:57.902
Capitalist Emulsification
to play my wedding.

03:57.904 --> 03:59.904
Then I guess we have nothing
left to talk about, here.

03:59.906 --> 04:01.439
I was this close
to having

04:01.441 --> 04:03.308
the Mountain West's
premier ska band.

04:03.310 --> 04:04.709
Skaffirmative Action?

04:04.711 --> 04:06.511
I know.
I couldn't believe it either.

04:06.513 --> 04:08.580
And stupid Cory forgot
to pay the deposit,

04:08.582 --> 04:10.048
and they just
bailed on the gig.

04:10.050 --> 04:12.184
You dodged a bullet.
First of all, ska sucks.

04:12.186 --> 04:14.586
Second of all, those guys
are wicked dickheads.

04:14.588 --> 04:16.388
How do you know
they're wicked dickheads?

04:16.390 --> 04:17.255
Because I knew them.

04:17.257 --> 04:18.857
[ Scoffs ]
Yeah, right.

04:18.859 --> 04:22.060
Capitalist Emulsification
and Skaffirmative Action

04:22.062 --> 04:25.864
had the most bitter blood feud
the front range has ever seen.

04:25.866 --> 04:28.467
Then it came to a head
in '99 -- Warped Tour.

04:28.469 --> 04:29.934
There was one spot left

04:29.936 --> 04:32.471
on the coveted
Mesa Boogie Rehydration Stage,

04:32.473 --> 04:34.539
and they gave it
to Skaffirmative Action.

04:34.541 --> 04:36.941
Shoemaker, you have to
ask Skaffirmative Action

04:36.943 --> 04:38.410
to play at my wedding.
No way!

04:38.412 --> 04:39.944
God damn it, Shoemaker.

04:39.946 --> 04:41.613
I'm trying to be
the white knight
for my bride, okay?

04:41.615 --> 04:43.682
Jade never had anything
growing up.

04:43.684 --> 04:45.484
Skaffirmative Action
could save this thing.

04:45.486 --> 04:46.885
Dude, I'm sorry, but --

04:46.887 --> 04:49.287
You know, I still haven't
chosen my best man.

04:49.289 --> 04:50.355
Hmm?

04:50.357 --> 04:51.890
Really?
Yeah.

04:51.892 --> 04:55.960
And you think something like
this could get me an offer?

04:55.962 --> 04:57.496
I'm just saying
swallowing your pride

04:57.498 --> 05:00.432
and booking the groom's
favorite band,

05:00.434 --> 05:04.102
that sounds like some
real best man shit to me.

05:04.104 --> 05:05.637
Fine. Yeah, I'll do it.

05:05.639 --> 05:07.439
Oh, my God.
Jade is gonna lose her mind!

05:07.441 --> 05:08.640
Okay. All right.
Thank you.

05:08.642 --> 05:09.975
Ohh!
Thank you.

05:15.115 --> 05:17.416
What the hell was that?

05:19.453 --> 05:20.985
♪♪

05:20.987 --> 05:23.255
Yes, I was arrested.

05:23.257 --> 05:26.258
But, listen, the prostitute
that I bought

05:26.260 --> 05:29.161
is now marrying her john,
so it --

05:30.865 --> 05:34.199
You know, I expect that kind
of exclusionary garbage

05:34.201 --> 05:35.333
from the Methodists,

05:35.335 --> 05:37.536
but not from you!
[ Receiver slams ]

05:37.538 --> 05:38.803
Is everything okay
in here, Geoffrey?

05:38.805 --> 05:42.006
The Universalist Life Church
revoked my ordainment!

05:42.008 --> 05:43.341
I'm defrocked!

05:43.343 --> 05:44.943
Well, it sounds to me like
you better get a new religion.

05:44.945 --> 05:46.344
I'm gonna have to start
cold calling

05:46.346 --> 05:47.279
every church in town

05:47.281 --> 05:48.613
is what I'm going
to have to do.

05:48.615 --> 05:50.883
Someone will vest
the power in me.

05:53.019 --> 05:56.388
Tammy, are those flowers
from a VA cemetery?

05:58.092 --> 05:59.091
No.

05:59.093 --> 06:02.127
Where are all the cans?

06:03.630 --> 06:05.497
Must be a goat on the loose.

06:05.499 --> 06:08.032
[ Cans rattling ]

06:08.034 --> 06:09.902
A human goat.

06:09.904 --> 06:12.504
Hey!
Where'd you get those cans?

06:12.506 --> 06:15.039
♪♪

06:15.041 --> 06:16.441
I'm on a can hunt!

06:16.443 --> 06:19.578
Come back!
I just have questions!

06:19.580 --> 06:22.915
It's one of many reasons
why you're like the stone jade.

06:22.917 --> 06:26.251
N-No! I told you Max,
no fedoras.

06:26.253 --> 06:27.586
Indeed, you did,
my good man.

06:27.588 --> 06:29.387
But this is a trilby.

06:29.389 --> 06:30.923
Abbey, quit messaging
your cyber boyfriend

06:30.925 --> 06:32.124
and get your head in the game.

06:32.126 --> 06:34.793
It's an anonymous,
online, platonic pen-pal.

06:34.795 --> 06:36.395
Okay, I'm hearing a lot
of talk about Abbey

06:36.397 --> 06:38.263
and not, "What does
my client Loren need"?

06:38.265 --> 06:39.598
Jesus Christ!

06:39.600 --> 06:41.600
Are you sewing the pants
directly to my leg, Max?

06:41.602 --> 06:42.667
Sorry, my liege.

06:42.669 --> 06:44.002
Chili's can suck it,
all right?

06:44.004 --> 06:45.070
There's a new app king
in town!

06:45.072 --> 06:47.072
I present to you
Mac and Cheese shooters.

06:47.074 --> 06:49.073
Loren:
Oh, God, no.

06:49.075 --> 06:50.743
Uh, this is macaroni
in a Dixie cup.

06:50.745 --> 06:52.811
Unh-unh-unh.
It's a shooter.

06:52.813 --> 06:53.878
It's elevated.

06:53.880 --> 06:54.879
I don't think you understand

06:54.881 --> 06:56.415
the concept of elevation.

06:56.417 --> 06:58.550
Think lobster...
Yes!

06:58.552 --> 07:00.753
...cremini mushrooms...
Cremini mushrooms
would be fantastic.

07:00.755 --> 07:02.554
Cremini mushrooms?
Yes!

07:02.556 --> 07:03.956
Hey, baby.

07:03.958 --> 07:05.290
Oh, hey, Jade.
Brought you those graded
tests you left at home.

07:05.292 --> 07:07.359
Thank you so much.
Mwah.

07:07.361 --> 07:09.094
Ooh, I like the pants.
They're looking good.

07:09.096 --> 07:10.162
I can totally see
your bulge.

07:10.164 --> 07:11.363
No. Come on.

07:11.365 --> 07:13.165
They're no Tom Ford,
but they'll have to do --

07:13.167 --> 07:15.033
one of many compromises.

07:15.035 --> 07:16.701
Babe, I keep telling you
I don't need a big wedding.

07:16.703 --> 07:18.570
We can just elope.
Nonsense!

07:18.572 --> 07:19.838
You've dreamed
of a fairytale wedding

07:19.840 --> 07:21.105
ever since you were
a little girl.

07:21.107 --> 07:22.907
I never wanted that.
Since you were a little girl.

07:22.909 --> 07:24.843
And now these people
are blowing it.

07:24.845 --> 07:25.978
So how does that feel?
Okay.

07:25.980 --> 07:27.179
Well, I got
to get back to work.

07:27.181 --> 07:28.647
Those Japanese businessmen
aren't gonna bukkake themselves.

07:28.649 --> 07:30.983
I'll walk you out.
I will walk you out.

07:30.985 --> 07:32.785
Your prince charming
could use a little air.

07:32.787 --> 07:35.320
Oh, there are the two
lovebirds right there!

07:35.322 --> 07:36.989
[ Laughs ] Looking forward
to marrying you guys!

07:36.991 --> 07:39.324
Everything
is right on track!

07:39.326 --> 07:41.460
We have got a disaster
on our hands.

07:41.462 --> 07:42.661
What is it?

07:42.663 --> 07:44.929
Just my minister's license
was revoked,

07:44.931 --> 07:46.931
and now the entire
wedding is ruined.

07:46.933 --> 07:47.800
What?!

07:47.802 --> 07:50.202
Aaaaaah!

07:50.204 --> 07:51.737
Fix this.

07:53.674 --> 07:57.810
[ Whimpers ]

08:00.381 --> 08:04.783
Sir!
Just a second!

08:04.785 --> 08:06.051
♪♪

08:06.053 --> 08:07.219
[ Imitates tires squealing ]

08:09.056 --> 08:10.722
Come back!
I'm nice!

08:10.724 --> 08:13.458
♪♪

08:13.460 --> 08:15.861
Oh, wow.

08:18.265 --> 08:20.265
SuckTown!

08:20.267 --> 08:22.868
I always thought
it was a myth, but it's real.

08:22.870 --> 08:25.604
As real as the flood-control
pump it's named after.

08:25.606 --> 08:27.406
But we prefer SuTo.

08:27.408 --> 08:29.541
Neighborhood's trying
to re-brand.

08:29.543 --> 08:31.476
Like FroYo.
Totally get it.

08:31.478 --> 08:34.279
[ Chuckles, gasps ]
Whoa.

08:34.281 --> 08:36.215
Looks like I found
the mother lode.

08:36.217 --> 08:37.416
Where did you get
all those cans?

08:37.418 --> 08:39.018
That is a hobo secret.

08:39.020 --> 08:40.285
Look,
I have a can emergency.

08:40.287 --> 08:43.889
I'll pay you
for the hobo secret.

08:43.891 --> 08:46.425
Well,
I can see you're serious.

08:46.427 --> 08:47.626
Tell you what.

08:47.628 --> 08:50.762
Take that money,
buy us a 12-pack of beer,

08:50.764 --> 08:53.164
we'll tell you all the secrets
of getting cans.

08:53.166 --> 08:55.700
Eliminate the middleman.
I like it.

08:55.702 --> 08:57.036
I just hope there's
a place to buy liquor

08:57.038 --> 08:59.038
in this bad neighborhood.

08:59.040 --> 09:04.375
♪♪

09:04.377 --> 09:08.580
Whoa!
Oh, my ska'd.

09:08.582 --> 09:10.249
Billy Shoemaker.
How's it going, asshole?

09:10.251 --> 09:11.250
Hey, Scott.

09:11.252 --> 09:13.252
Pronounced "Skatt."

09:13.254 --> 09:14.920
Oh, yeah. "Skatt."

09:14.922 --> 09:16.721
Yeah, got it
legally changed in court.

09:16.723 --> 09:17.723
Yeah, that's great.

09:17.725 --> 09:18.857
And you look like
you literally

09:18.859 --> 09:21.192
can't stop partying
like it's 1999.

09:21.194 --> 09:23.262
Can't skap, won't skap.
[stop]

09:23.264 --> 09:25.797
Yeah, I forgot
about all the ska puns.

09:25.799 --> 09:28.199
Listen, my buddy's
getting married,

09:28.201 --> 09:30.469
and he loves your stupid
band for some reason.

09:30.471 --> 09:31.736
You were gonna play
his wedding.

09:31.738 --> 09:33.538
I'm going to skap you
right there.

09:33.540 --> 09:36.875
Skaffirmative Action
is no more.

09:36.877 --> 09:38.810
I had to fire P-Riddle
this morning.

09:38.812 --> 09:41.212
The dancing guy?
What the hell did he do?

09:41.214 --> 09:42.881
He sent his skattorney
after me --

09:42.883 --> 09:44.483
trying to get
a songwriting credit

09:44.485 --> 09:47.086
for on of our hit songs,
"Third Trimester Skabortion."

09:47.088 --> 09:49.354
Yeah, Scott,
I don't care, okay?

09:49.356 --> 09:51.890
Just play without him,
please.

09:51.892 --> 09:53.558
No skan do, skaballero.

09:53.560 --> 09:56.027
A ska band
without a dancing guy?

09:56.029 --> 09:58.697
It's like a wallet
without a chain -- useless.

09:58.699 --> 10:01.766
That is the most ridiculous
thing I've never heard.

10:01.768 --> 10:02.701
[ Snaps fingers ]
Skedaddle.

10:02.703 --> 10:05.236
Don't you mean
skadaddle?
No.

10:05.238 --> 10:07.238
You missed it.
No, I didn't.

10:07.240 --> 10:08.173
Yeah, you did!

10:08.175 --> 10:12.043
[ Breathing heavily ]
Hey! Here.

10:12.045 --> 10:14.179
One 12-pack of beer,
good sirs.

10:14.181 --> 10:16.181
About time.

10:16.183 --> 10:17.649
Oh.
Almost forgot your change.

10:17.651 --> 10:20.219
[ Chuckles ]

10:21.922 --> 10:22.921
[ Can pops ]

10:22.923 --> 10:25.624
Ready for that
hobo can secret.

10:28.662 --> 10:31.396
If you could just tell me
where to get some cans.

10:31.398 --> 10:34.099
[ Burps ]

10:36.069 --> 10:39.204
No rush.
Just a best friend emergency.

10:39.206 --> 10:40.939
Ah.

10:40.941 --> 10:43.809
[ Can clatters ]
Now, about them cans.

10:43.811 --> 10:45.210
Okay.

10:45.212 --> 10:46.745
Rufus here's got a whole trove
stored in a water tower,

10:46.747 --> 10:48.680
but he won't tell us where
'cause he don't trust us.

10:48.682 --> 10:51.883
That's right.
Goddamn lizard people.

10:51.885 --> 10:54.219
And he can't get them himself
on account of the missing leg.

10:54.221 --> 10:56.488
Who took his leg?
Damn wild dogs.

10:56.490 --> 10:58.623
Been terrorizing
SuckTown for years.

10:58.625 --> 10:59.624
SuTo!

10:59.626 --> 11:01.092
I was born here,

11:01.094 --> 11:02.427
and I'll call it
SuckTown

11:02.429 --> 11:04.229
If I want to call it
SuckTown.

11:04.231 --> 11:06.097
Get my leg back,

11:06.099 --> 11:07.699
I'll get you all the cans
you can carry.

11:07.701 --> 11:08.700
Wow!

11:08.702 --> 11:10.135
This is just like
a video game.

11:13.907 --> 11:16.307
How is that guy
not homeless?

11:16.309 --> 11:18.977
♪♪

11:18.979 --> 11:21.780
Hey, Phil.
You got a second?

11:21.782 --> 11:22.914
Not really.

11:22.916 --> 11:27.652
I just had a few questions
about your religion.

11:27.654 --> 11:28.920
I would've never
pegged you as a man

11:28.922 --> 11:30.589
that was interested
in the Church of Satan.

11:30.591 --> 11:32.191
Don't be ashamed.

11:32.193 --> 11:33.859
A lot of people bristle
when they hear the word "Satan."

11:33.861 --> 11:37.729
But we believe he represents
pride and individualism.

11:37.731 --> 11:38.864
You know, Anton LaVey --
That's great.

11:38.866 --> 11:40.532
Can I be ordained to marry
someone in your church

11:40.534 --> 11:42.601
in time for Loren's wedding?
Well, why didn't you say so?

11:42.603 --> 11:44.603
If we're gonna
fast-track this,

11:44.605 --> 11:46.938
we're going to have to send
a vial of your blood

11:46.940 --> 11:49.340
to HQ in Poughkeepsie.

11:49.342 --> 11:51.010
Real blood?
Yes.

11:51.012 --> 11:52.411
This will be quick.

11:52.413 --> 11:53.344
But it will hurt.

11:53.346 --> 11:55.346
[ Whimpers ]

11:55.348 --> 11:58.417
[ Sings indistinctly ]

11:58.419 --> 11:59.951
Aaaaah.

11:59.953 --> 12:01.620
I don't want to do it,
I don't want to do it,

12:01.622 --> 12:03.088
I don't want to do it,
I don't want to do it.

12:03.090 --> 12:04.489
♪♪

12:04.491 --> 12:06.892
I call it
the "Neat Joseph."

12:06.894 --> 12:09.828
It's a Sloppy Joe,
but I've removed the slop.

12:09.830 --> 12:11.230
I'm sorry, Rod.

12:11.232 --> 12:12.363
Were you under the impression
that my wedding

12:12.365 --> 12:14.433
is taking place
at a trailer park?!

12:14.435 --> 12:16.101
No, I was under the impression
it was taking place

12:16.103 --> 12:18.036
in a high school
gymnasium, Loren.

12:18.038 --> 12:19.504
You want to go, Rod?
Yeah, I would love to go!

12:19.506 --> 12:21.907
It's a big day!
What my client is trying to say

12:21.909 --> 12:24.910
is that maybe you could,
you know, fancy it up.

12:24.912 --> 12:26.311
You know,
the Marine in me

12:26.313 --> 12:28.780
wants to tell this prick
to sit on it!

12:28.782 --> 12:32.117
But the chef in me really wants
to rise to this challenge.

12:33.921 --> 12:35.587
All right, here's your tux.

12:35.589 --> 12:36.855
I'm sorry.

12:36.857 --> 12:38.657
Does this make me look like
I'm going to the BET Awards?

12:38.659 --> 12:40.859
No, it does not.
And that's the problem.

12:40.861 --> 12:41.860
She doesn't listen.

12:41.862 --> 12:43.128
Please have your kids
do it again.

12:43.130 --> 12:44.596
Yeah,
except good this time.

12:44.598 --> 12:46.131
All right, you want
to come at me, Payton?

12:46.133 --> 12:47.398
You are blowing it right now.

12:47.400 --> 12:49.334
Grow up!
Go back and have them
do it again.

12:49.336 --> 12:51.002
Loren.

12:51.004 --> 12:52.737
What?
Can you dial it
back a little bit?

12:52.739 --> 12:54.005
You're becoming Groomzilla.
[ Scoffs ]

12:54.007 --> 12:56.407
Oh, am I a Groomzilla?
This is me at a four!

12:56.409 --> 12:58.209
Act like a real
wedding planner.

12:58.211 --> 12:59.611
You wanted the job,
you got the job.

12:59.613 --> 13:01.012
Here's another centerpiece.

13:01.014 --> 13:02.748
Are these from
a children's hospital?

13:02.750 --> 13:04.816
