with mayonnaise?

14:11.285 --> 14:13.618
Finally, Tammy,
these arrangements are rustic,

14:13.620 --> 14:14.753
yet refined.

14:14.755 --> 14:16.421
About as rustic
and refined as that field

14:16.423 --> 14:18.156
by my house where
that Blockbuster used to be.

14:18.158 --> 14:20.959
Food, check.
Flowers, check. Band...

14:20.961 --> 14:23.896
Checkity-check, check,
a-checkity-check!

14:23.898 --> 14:26.699
Checkered pants.
Checkered past.

14:26.701 --> 14:27.900
Is that
Skaffirmative Action?

14:27.902 --> 14:29.501
You bet your skass it is.

14:29.503 --> 14:33.572
The Rocky Mountain Region's
most diverse ska band.

14:33.574 --> 14:35.373
No other
Rocky Mountain ska band

14:35.375 --> 14:37.842
has done more
to promote equality

14:37.844 --> 14:39.511
than these guys right here.

14:39.513 --> 14:43.115
That's right.
Old Shoemaker pulled it off.

14:43.117 --> 14:44.116
[ Laughs ]

14:44.118 --> 14:46.451
And all it cost me

14:46.453 --> 14:50.122
was every last shred
of musical integrity

14:50.124 --> 14:51.189
that I have ever had.

14:51.191 --> 14:52.124
Hey!
Hey, hey, hey, hey!

14:52.126 --> 14:54.126
What? What?
God!

14:54.128 --> 14:56.394
Dancing guy does not
touch the mic!

14:56.396 --> 14:58.196
Hey,
little miss size zero.

14:58.198 --> 14:59.264
I know you're busy,

14:59.266 --> 15:00.732
but I got to do
the final alterations,

15:00.734 --> 15:04.269
and Jade just conveniently had
to run a last minute errand --

15:04.271 --> 15:06.338
probably in SuckTown,
if you know what I mean.

15:06.340 --> 15:08.740
[ Sighs ]
I need a body in that dress.

15:08.742 --> 15:10.342
Oh, uh...

15:10.344 --> 15:11.676
Let's go.

15:11.678 --> 15:13.612
Game day, dude.

15:13.614 --> 15:15.547
Everything's gonna be great.

15:15.549 --> 15:18.216
Nothing can go
disastrously wrong.

15:18.218 --> 15:19.551
[ Knock on door ]
Baby boy.

15:19.553 --> 15:20.953
Jade!

15:20.955 --> 15:22.687
We're not supposed to see
each other before the wedding.

15:22.689 --> 15:23.956
It's fine.

15:23.958 --> 15:26.691
I cannot believe the lengths
you went to for this wedding.

15:26.693 --> 15:28.226
Skaffirmative Action
is here!

15:28.228 --> 15:29.361
What?

15:29.363 --> 15:31.296
I mean, I-I know!

15:31.298 --> 15:32.897
Yeah, everything
looks so beautiful.

15:32.899 --> 15:35.567
Well, I keep telling you you
deserve a fairytale wedding.

15:35.569 --> 15:37.369
I'm just scared you have
expectations I can't fulfill.

15:37.371 --> 15:39.904
Shh! Shush!

15:39.906 --> 15:42.775
Look, I know our relationship
might be un-traditional --

15:42.777 --> 15:44.443
you're a prostitute,
I'm a teacher.

15:44.445 --> 15:47.045
We're both renegades
playing by our own rules.

15:47.047 --> 15:49.047
I'm not asking you to be
something that you're not, Jade.

15:49.049 --> 15:51.183
I'm asking to marry you --
the real you --

15:51.185 --> 15:52.851
'cause that's what
I fell in love with.

15:52.853 --> 15:54.319
Want me to eat
your butt one last time

15:54.321 --> 15:56.321
while the church
still frowns upon it?

15:56.323 --> 15:57.790
Oh, hell, yes!
Yes, go!

15:57.792 --> 15:59.123
All right,
let me get that belt off.
Take your pants off.

15:59.125 --> 16:00.058
-There's my girl.
-Yes!

16:00.060 --> 16:01.126
Okay, all right.

16:01.128 --> 16:02.527
Jade!

16:02.529 --> 16:03.862
Don't you knock?
I've been looking
all over for you!

16:03.864 --> 16:06.064
Where have you been?
Oh, wow, Abbey.

16:06.066 --> 16:08.132
You're in my wedding dress.
Why?
No, no, no, no.

16:08.134 --> 16:10.669
I was filling in for you
until I found you,

16:10.671 --> 16:13.071
but then Leslie's kids
sewed the zipper on wrong,

16:13.073 --> 16:15.273
and now I'm stuck in it!

16:15.275 --> 16:16.608
You don't happen to have
anything else white

16:16.610 --> 16:17.876
that you can wear,
do you?

16:17.878 --> 16:19.077
I do have
a spare dress in my car.

16:19.079 --> 16:20.412
It's part of the
November Rain package.

16:20.414 --> 16:21.613
It's big with widowers.

16:21.615 --> 16:23.682
So I will just
go slip that on.

16:23.684 --> 16:25.217
Great.
Yes.

16:25.219 --> 16:27.686
Fairbell: I did it!

16:27.688 --> 16:32.224
Wow. Giving a dog a bone is not
like it is in the cartoons,

16:32.226 --> 16:33.826
but I got your leg,

16:33.828 --> 16:35.894
and just in time
for the wedding.

16:35.896 --> 16:38.030
That ain't my leg.
What?!

16:38.032 --> 16:39.364
Do I look Swedish to you?

16:39.366 --> 16:40.699
Whose leg is this?

16:40.701 --> 16:42.234
Could be anyone's.

16:42.236 --> 16:45.370
Goddamn lizard people
sneak in here at night

16:45.372 --> 16:47.972
